The paper deals with image cropping, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The proposed method uses reinforcement learning, which falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also mentions the use of actor-critic architecture, which is a popular deep learning technique, and hence it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper emphasizes the importance of aesthetics in image cropping, which could make it relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on several popular datasets, which could make it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
